-If you are experiencing any symptoms, please stay home.
-If you have been tested for Covid-19 in the past couple of days, you need to stay home until you receive your results. -

post_text:
A note from our Curriculum Director:

Hello Parents and Community Members! While this is an uncertain time, we are working hard to deliver instructional support to all of our students! This past week we had kids read and respond to a quick activity! Moving forward we are introducing a real world problem this week that is interdisciplinary! That means we have included, math, reading, writing, science, social studies and the arts into the problem that our students should solve! Creating solutions is one of the highest levels of thinking, so we want to challenge our students to be creative, use critical thinking and have fun this week.

If you have curriculum questions, please email me CheriBorchardt@lorenaisd.net. Remember take care of you and your family! It is indeed a great day to be a Leopard!!!!

Lorena Elementary School is at AT&T Stadium.
December 17, 2019 at 2:05 PM · Arlington, TX ·

Today our 5th grade students had the privilege of taking a field trip to visit AT&T Stadium in Arlington, home of the Dallas Cowboys! Our tour guides educated our students on the technology and engineering that went in to building this magnificent structure, as well as some of the history regarding America’s Team.

shared_text:
Lorena Elementary School
August 26, 2019 at 5:47 PM ·

Tomorrow night, Tue August 27, is our Parent Orientation Event.
